[40.023623, "o", "\r\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n  ACT 3: Experiment вЂ” Iteration 2\r\nв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓв”Ѓ\r\n\r\n"]
[42.026725, "o", "$ ddx agent run --text \"Continue optimizing src/process.js. This is iteration 2.\r\n\r\nRead the current src/p...\"\r\n\r\n"]
[64.161328, "o", "**Change:** Replaced the character-by-character uppercase loop with `item.toUpperCase()` вЂ” eliminating O(n) per-character calls and O(nВІ) string concatenation allocations.\r\n\r\n**METRIC:** `runtime=8.0ms`\r\n\r\n**KEEP.** This is a significant improvement. For reference, the iteration 1 code (with the Set but still the inner loop) would have been considerably slower вЂ” the native `toUpperCase()` on the full string is far more efficient than per-character processing with repeated concatenation.\r\n\r\n"]
[67.162765, "o", "After iteration 2:\r\n$ npm test\r\n"]
[67.532327, "o", "\r\n> perf-lab@1.0.0 test\r\n> node --test\r\n\r\n"]
[67.74263, "o", "в–¶ processStrings\r\n  \u001b[32mвњ” uppercases all items \u001b[90m(1.247872ms)\u001b[39m\u001b[39m\r\n"]
[67.743466, "o", "  \u001b[32mвњ” deduplicates results \u001b[90m(0.120559ms)\u001b[39m\u001b[39m\r\n  \u001b[32mвњ” handles empty input \u001b[90m(0.106739ms)\u001b[39m\u001b[39m\r\n"]
[67.743875, "o", "  \u001b[32mвњ” handles single character strings \u001b[90m(0.226207ms)\u001b[39m\u001b[39m\r\n\u001b[32mв–¶ \u001b[39mprocessStrings \u001b[90m(3.959039ms)\u001b[39m\r\n\r\n"]
